The '''Accokeek''' were a group of [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]] living in [[Southern Maryland]] at the time of English colonization.  They lived along the [[Potomac River]] in present-day [[Prince George's County, Maryland]].  They were an [[Algonquian languages|Algonquian]]-language tribe and were related to the [[Piscataway tribe|Piscataway]], another [[Algonquian languages|Algonquian]]-language tribe.

[[Accokeek, Maryland]], a small unincorporated town in Maryland, was named for the Accokeek<ref>{{cite book|author=Bright, William|title=Native American Placenames of the United States|page=21|date=2004|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press|ISBN=0-8061-3576-X}}</ref> tribe.

Accokeek means at the edge of the hill.

