'''Azor LeBlanc''' (October 27, 1927 - July 31, 2011) is a former business owner and political figure in [[New Brunswick]], Canada. He represented [[Shediac-Cap-Pelé|Shediac]] in the [[Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick]] from 1974 to 1991 as a [[Liberal Party of New Brunswick|Liberal]] member.
He was born in [[Cap-Pelé, New Brunswick]], the son of Thaddée LeBlanc, and educated at [[University of St. Joseph's College|St. Joseph's College]]. In 1948, he married Rose Leger with whom he had ten children. LeBlanc owned and operated a drive-in, motel and store. He served on the council for [[Westmorland County, New Brunswick|Westmorland County]].
LeBlanc died at the Dr. Georges-L.-Dumont University Hospital Centre in [[Moncton, New Brunswick]] on July 31, 2011, after suffering from [[cancer]] for 33 years.<ref>[http://timestranscript.canadaeast.com/news/article/1428876 Late Shediac-Cap-Pelé MLA was a pillar of his community] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321221102/http://timestranscript.canadaeast.com/news/article/1428876 |date=March 21, 2012 }}</ref>
