'''Jesinta Franklin''' (née '''Campbell''')<ref>https://www.instagram.com/jesinta_franklin/</ref> (born 12 August 1991) is an Australian TV Host, model and beauty pageant titleholder. Franklin won [[Miss Universe Australia|Miss Universe Australia 2010]] and represented [[Australia]] at [[Miss Universe 2010]], placing 2nd Runner-Up.

==Early life==
Jesinta Franklin grew up in [[Gold Coast, Queensland]], and attended [[Aquinas College, Southport|Aquinas College]] through her schooling years.<ref>{{cite web| last=Strebe  | first=Sacha| title=Jesinta Campbell: reliving the journey | publisher=goldcoast.com.au| date=25 August 2010| url=http://www.goldcoast.com.au/article/2010/08/25/250175_more-gold-coast-gig-guide.html| accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref>

==Beauty pageant career==
Franklin was crowned as Miss Universe Australia 2010 on 17 June 2010 representing [[Queensland]]. She later competed at the [[Miss Universe 2010|2010]] edition of the Miss Universe pageant on 23 August 2010 and finished as the 2nd Runner-Up behind [[Yendi Phillipps]] ([[Jamaica]]) and winner [[Ximena Navarrete]] ([[Mexico]]).<ref>[http://misscontest.blogspot.com/2010/08/final-results-miss-universe-2010.html Announce Final Results Mexico - Jimena Navarrete Miss Universe 2010]</ref> She was also designated Miss Congeniality at this pageant.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/confidential/australias-jesinta-campbell-in-final-15-of-miss-universe-finals-in-las-vegas/story-e6frf96o-1225909371134 | title=Australia's Jesinta Campbell wins Miss Congeniality at Miss Universe finals in Las Vegas | author=AAP | date=25 August 2010 | accessdate=3 July 2011 }}</ref>

==Media career==
Franklin (as Jesinta Campbell) published her first book, ''Live a Beautiful Life'',  in October 2016 <ref>http://www.booktopia.com.au/live-a-beautiful-life-jesinta-campbell/prod9780733635700.html</ref>

===Television===
In September 2010, she became a guest reporter for entertainment and fashion subjects on [[Seven Network]]'s ''[[The Morning Show (TV program)|The Morning Show]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/fashion/miss-universe-runner-up-jesinta-campbell-joins-channel-sevens-morning-show/story-e6frfn7i-1225914593654 |title=Miss Universe runner-up Jesinta Campbell joins Channel Seven's Morning Show |first=Rosie |last=Squires |newspaper=The Sunday Mail |location=Queensland |date=5 September 2010 |accessdate=3 July 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100914133612/http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/fashion/miss-universe-runner-up-jesinta-campbell-joins-channel-sevens-morning-show/story-e6frfn7i-1225914593654 |archivedate=14 September 2010 |df= }}</ref>

In October 2011, she appeared as a contestant on the [[Nine Network]]'s ''[[The Celebrity Apprentice Australia]]'' as a member of Team Unity.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2011/11/julia-morris-wins-celebrity-apprentice-2011.html | title=Julia Morris wins Celebrity Apprentice 2011 | date=21 November 2011 | publisher=TV Tonight | first=David | last=Knox | accessdate=26 November 2011}}</ref>

===Radio===
Franklin appeared on the [[Hot30 Countdown]] on 3 January 2012 and filled in for Maude Garrett with Matty Acton for one week. She came back as Matty Acton's co-host on 27 February 2012 on the Hot30 Countdown.{{Citation needed|date=July 2017}}

==Personal life==
Jesinta Franklin is married to [[Australian rules football]] player [[Lance Franklin]], who plays for the [[Sydney Swans]] in the [[Australian Football League]] (AFL).<ref>{{cite web| last=Clarke| first=Jenna| title=Lance 'Buddy' Franklin and Jesinta Campbell engaged | publisher=The Sydney Morning Herald| date=21 December 2014| url=http://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/celebrity/lance-buddy-franklin-and-jesinta-campbell-engaged-20141221-12bpgs.html| accessdate=21 December 2014}}</ref> They married in November 2016 in a private ceremony with close friends and family.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/celebrity-life/jesinta-campbell-posts-first-picture-of-wedding-to-buddy-franklin/news-story/b6a9f650c90bddbb5f8b202ab3b64242|title=‘Mr and Mrs Franklin’|newspaper=NewsComAu|access-date=2016-11-05}}</ref>

